    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a two-level hierarchical structure with 4 parent nodes (geographical regions) and 13 child nodes (provinces/territories). Primary variables include categorical region names (nominal scale) and numerical area measurements (ratio scale) ranging from 5,660 to 2,093,190 km\u00b2. Data quality is considered high as it mirrors official statistics from Wikipedia, though values should be verified against current governmental sources. The treemap visualization adheres to Tufte's principles by maximizing data-ink through direct area encoding without redundant decoration. Cairo's perceptual principles are applied through: 1) Pre-attentive color coding for regional differentiation 2) Size-based magnitude estimation 3) Hierarchical grouping via containment. Statistical coherence is maintained with child nodes summing to parent totals (e.g., Northern Canada total = 482,443 + 1,346,106 + 2,093,190 = 3,921,739 km\u00b2). Color contrast ratios between regions exceed WCAG 2.1 AA requirements for accessibility."
